# 🎮 PIKAVERSE ASSET STANDARD PACK (BENNY LIST v1)

A **simple, beginner-friendly rulebook + starter kit structure** for all images, icons, and UI assets in your platform.

---

# 🧠 1. CORE RULE (SIMPLE VERSION)

> Every asset in Pikaverse must have:

* a clear purpose (what it is used for)
* a fixed size category (so everything aligns)
* a consistent naming style

---

# 📁 2. FOLDER STRUCTURE (FOR ORGANIZATION)

```
assets/
  icons/
  items/
  keys/
  ui/
  backgrounds/
  effects/
  templates/
```

---

# 🟨 3. SIZE STANDARDS (THE GOLD RULES)

## 🎯 ICONS (items, rewards, objects)

* Size: **48 × 48 px**
* Use: inventory, rewards, item lists

---

## 🔑 KEYS (special unlock items)

* Size: **48 × 48 px**
* Rare/legendary: up to **64 × 64 px**

---

## 😊 UI EMOJIS / SMALL REACTIONS

* Size: **24 × 24 px**
* Use: buttons, alerts, feedback

---

## 🧭 NODE / MAP ICONS (editor only)

* Size: **32 × 32 px**

---

## 🔘 BUTTON ICONS

* Size: **32 × 32 px or 40 × 40 px**
* Use: play, save, delete, settings

---

## 🌄 BACKGROUNDS (LEVEL SCENES)

* Size: **1920 × 1080 px (standard)**
* Optional high-res: **2560 × 1440 px**

---

# 🧠 4. NAMING RULES (VERY IMPORTANT)

## ✔ Use simple lowercase + underscores:

### GOOD:

* gold_key.png
* ruby_key.png
* healing_potion.png
* mystery_box.png

### BAD:

* GoldKey.PNG
* ruby-key-final-v2.png
* IMAGE123.png

